---
import PublicLayout from '../layouts/PublicLayout.astro'
import { SITE_URL } from '../lib/site'
---
<PublicLayout
  title="About DegreeWiki"
  description="Learn what DegreeWiki is, how we collect and verify education data, and how Fit Finder works."
  canonical={SITE_URL + '/about'}
>
  <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">

    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">About DegreeWiki</h1>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">What is DegreeWiki?</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
        DegreeWiki is an education information platform for international students. It helps you
        discover and compare university programs, scholarships, and study-abroad guides from
        institutions around the world.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">What DegreeWiki is not</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-600">
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-gray-400 shrink-0">&mdash;</span>Not an official university or admissions office</li>
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-gray-400 shrink-0">&mdash;</span>Not a scholarship provider or funding body</li>
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-gray-400 shrink-0">&mdash;</span>Not a government or immigration authority</li>
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-gray-400 shrink-0">&mdash;</span>Not a legal, financial, or visa advisor</li>
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-gray-400 shrink-0">&mdash;</span>Not an official admissions assessor</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">How we collect and verify data</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-3">
        Information on DegreeWiki is gathered from official university and scholarship websites and
        published by the DegreeWiki team. Where possible, each entry includes a verification status
        and a link to the official source so you can check details directly.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
        Program details, tuition fees, admission requirements, deadlines, scholarship eligibility,
        and visa policies can change without notice. Always confirm important details with the
        official university, scholarship provider, or government website before applying.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Fit Finder</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
        Fit Finder is a tool that helps you explore programs that may align with your study
        preferences. It uses rule-based matching on preferences you save — such as your target
        degree level, subjects, preferred countries, and budget. Results show preference alignment
        only. They are not admissions assessments, eligibility determinations, or predictions of
        any outcome.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">AI features</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
        DegreeWiki is building AI-assisted features to help students explore and understand
        education options. When available, these features will be assistive tools based on
        available DegreeWiki context. They will not replace official sources or guarantee any
        outcome. Always verify AI-suggested information with the relevant official source.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Corrections and feedback</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
        We welcome corrections to outdated or inaccurate information. A public contact and
        correction channel will be added before launch. Until then, users should verify important
        details directly with official sources.
      </p>
    </section>

    <div class="mt-10 pt-6 border-t border-gray-100 flex flex-wrap gap-4 text-sm">
      <a href="/disclaimer" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Disclaimer</a>
      <a href="/privacy"    class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Privacy</a>
      <a href="/terms"      class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Terms of Use</a>
    </div>

  </div>
</PublicLayout>
